9.description: textbox to Type and search for filters specific and relevant to companies. You can choose this button if you want to select filters related to company info ('Company', 'Account Location', '# Employees', 'Technologies' ,'Revenue', 'Funding', 'Founded Year','Industry & Keywords', 'Job Postings'). You can type and search for filters specific and relevant to Companies. You can choose this button if you want to select filters related to company info ('Company', 'Account Location', '# Employees', 'Technologies' ,'Revenue', 'Funding', 'Founded Year','Industry & Keywords' 'Job Postings'). If no filters are chosen in this step then proceed to Apply Filters.
9.type_description:
Based on the user input, type and select the filter strictly and only from the following options, Note only select ONE filter to type at a time : Company, Location, # Employees, Technologies ,Revenue, Lists, Funding, Industry & Keywords, Job Postings. Only type one filter at a single time. In case of multiple search filter criteria, proceed with one filter criteria and its required steps at a time, then add another filter using the more filters flow. 
 DON'T Leave this field empty. Always choose a filter from the OPTIONS.

51.description: textbox to Type and search for filters specific and relevant to People. You can choose this button if you want to select filters related to person info ('Time Zone', 'Job Titles', 'Total Years of Experience', 'Job change', 'Time in current role, Industry & Keywords', 'Job Postings'), Email Engagement activity (like 'Email Status', 'Email opened') and more. If no filters are chosen in this step then proceed to Apply Filters.
51.type_description:
Based on the user input, type a filter strictly and only from the following options, Note only type only ONE filter at a time: Job Titles, Time Zone, Total Years of Experience, Company, Email Status, Funding, Revenue, Technologies, # Employees, Industry & Keywords. 
 DON'T Leave this field empty. Always choose a filter from the OPTIONS.

10.description: Button to apply the selected filters. Choose this button if and only if all the filters under the People tab are selected.

108.description: Button to apply the selected filters. Choose this button if and only if all the filters under the Companies tab are selected.

95.description: If 'Job Postings' is typed in the search filter, then the user can select the Job Postings filter to search for companies which are currently hiring. This feature is crucial for targeting sales and marketing efforts more effectively. Users can pinpoint companies hiring for specific roles that may benefit from their products or services, assess the timing for outreach by identifying new job openings, and tailor their sales pitches to address the potential needs highlighted by the open positions. Additionally, this filter assists in market analysis, enabling users to observe industry trends and competitive dynamics.

96.description: Dropdown to type and specify particular job titles the user is interested in when searching for companies with job openings. It refines the search to roles relevant to the user’s offerings based on the input objective.
96.type_description: You should type in the job titles to filter companies that are hiring for the specific positions based on the input objective, aiding in targeted sales and marketing efforts. If and only In case of multiple job titles type them as a list of comma seperated values like ['manager', 'accountant'] else if in case of only one job title type it as a string like 'Manager'

97.description: This dropdown is used to filter job postings by geographic location. It enables users to focus on a specific area, which is particularly useful for location-based targeting as specified by the input objective to target companies which are hiring in a particular and specific location
97.type_description: You can type in the geographical locations to target companies which are hiring for given job titles in a specific location based on the input objective, to narrow down the job postings to a desired area. If and only In case of Multiple Locations ALWAYS type them  as a list of comma(,) separated values like ['India', 'London'] else in case of only one location type just the string like 'India'. In case abbreviated locations are specified then ALWAYS look up for the entire location or the closest match to that (for example if ND is given in the input, location should be North Dakota, OH is Ohio etc.) and so on

You should choose this button if and only in case more than one company domain or url is specified in the user input.You can select this button in case of more than one company/domain urls is specified by the input objective. If and only In case of more than one companies urls are specified to include in the user input, type the url of the companies as a list of comma separated values. For example if google and amazon both are specified you can type ['www.google.com, www.amazon.com'], If specific URLs of the companies are not provided then search the web for the best match for the URL domain, for e.g. if Seattle Textiles is specified then search the web and input 'www.seatex.com' and so on for other companies
